Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Line a
#baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce.

Remove @BBQ Baby Back Ribs{1} from package and place on prepared baking sheet.
Top ribs with any remaining sauce from package, then sprinkle with half the 
@Ancho Chili Powder{2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later). Top ribs with a second
sheet of foil; crimp edges of foil to create a packet.

Mince @Jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

== Cheddar Jalapeño Biscuits ==

Place 3 TBSP @Butter{3%tbsp} (6 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}.
Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine half the melted butter with 
@Cream Cheese{2%tbsp}, half the @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} (you'll use the rest later),
and up to half the jalapeño to taste.

Remove @Pillsbury™ Buttermilk Southern Homestyle Biscuits{1%6oz} from package.
Using a #rolling pin{}, roll out each biscuit into a 3-inch round.

Divide cheddar filling among biscuits. Using your fingers, fold over biscuits and
pinch to close. Gently roll each stuffed biscuit into a ball.

Place close together seam sides down on a second lightly oiled baking sheet.

Place sheet with ribs on middle rack; place sheet with biscuits on top rack.

Bake until ribs are warmed through and biscuits are golden and puffed,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep ribs covered until ready to serve.

Remove sheet with biscuits from oven; drizzle with remaining melted butter, then
sprinkle with remaining cheddar and remaining jalapeño to taste.

Return biscuits to top rack until dough is cooked through and cheese melts,
~{2-3%minutes} more. (It's OK if some cheese oozes out.)

== Charred Corn ==

Meanwhile, drain @Corn{13.4%oz}; pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
corn and remaining chili powder; cook, stirring occasionally, until corn is
charred, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Transfer to a large bowl. Set aside to cool.

> TIP: To help your corn cool down quicker, refrigerate until ready to use in next step.

== Corn Salad ==

Quarter @Grape Tomatoes{4}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}. Roughly chop
@Cilantro{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

Once charred corn has cooled to room temperature (or colder), stir in tomatoes,
scallions, @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tbsp}, half the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} (all for 4 servings),
half the cilantro, a squeeze of lime juice, and lime zest to taste. Season
generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Carefully remove and discard foil from ribs. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and
cut into individual pieces.

Garnish corn salad with remaining cilantro. Serve with biscuit bombs and
remaining lime wedges on the side.